[[Translation:en/Archive/Manual/Regional Investigator]]


The '''Regional Investigator''' is a government official who investigates improper or unethical behavior in business and provides oversight of the [[en/Manual/Local authority|local authorities]]. If he catches a [[en/Manual/Transport company|transport company]] [[en/Manual/Local authority#Pass_a_Bribe|bribing a local authority]], he will block that company's services for that area for six months, and prevent further interaction with that Local Authority.
